@startuml
title pyArchimate Context Diagram

"pyArchimate" as Library
actor "Designer" as Designer
actor "Automation / Integrations" as Automation
cloud "Archi / Archimate / ARIS sources" as Inputs
rectangle "Exchange Formats (XML, CSV)" as Outputs
rectangle "Format Adapters (IO)" as IO
rectangle "pyArchimate Core" as Core
rectangle "View Module\n(View, Node, Connection)" as ViewMod
rectangle "Logging Subsystem" as Logging

Designer --> Core : create models, add elements
Designer --> ViewMod : draw views, place nodes
Automation --> Core : trigger automation scripts
Core --> ViewMod : owns views
Core --> IO : delegate parsing & serialization
IO --> Inputs : parse external sources
IO --> Outputs : write output files
Core --> Logging : emit diagnostics
Core ..> Library : exposes Public API
Library ..> Inputs : references validation metadata
@enduml
